  "prompt": "What is the Golden Gate bridge named after?",
  "response": "The Golden Gate Bridge, located in San Francisco, California, is named after the Golden Gate Strait, which is the entrance to San Francisco Bay from the Pacific Ocean. The strait was named \"Golden Gate\" by Captain John C. Fr\u00e9mont in 1846, inspired by the golden-hued hillsides that surround the entrance and the idea that this passage might lead to great wealth and opportunity, much like the golden gates of a prosperous city. The bridge, completed in 1937, adopted this name because it spans the Golden Gate Strait.",
